@startuml Components-Architecture-Diagram
!theme plain
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

title Sistema de Gestión de Roles, Permisos y Suscripciones\nDiagrama de Componentes - Arquitectura

' ===============================================
' ESTILOS Y COLORES
' ===============================================

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor<<frontend>> #E3F2FD
    BorderColor<<frontend>> #1976D2
    BackgroundColor<<backend>> #F3E5F5
    BorderColor<<backend>> #7B1FA2
    BackgroundColor<<database>> #FFF3E0
    BorderColor<<database>> #F57C00
    BackgroundColor<<cache>> #E8F5E9
    BorderColor<<cache>> #388E3C
    BackgroundColor<<external>> #FCE4EC
    BorderColor<<external>> #C2185B
    BackgroundColor<<queue>> #FFF9C4
    BorderColor<<queue>> #F9A825
}

' ===============================================
' CAPA DE PRESENTACIÓN (FRONTEND)
' ===============================================

package "Frontend Layer" <<frontend>> {
    component "Angular App" as Angular {
        component [Auth Module] as AuthModule
        component [Dashboard Module] as DashboardModule
        component [Users Module] as UsersModule
        component [Roles Module] as RolesModule
        component [Billing Module] as BillingModule
        component [Settings Module] as SettingsModule

        component [Auth Interceptor] as AuthInterceptor
        component [Error Interceptor] as ErrorInterceptor
        component [Loading Interceptor] as LoadingInterceptor

        component [Auth Guard] as AuthGuard
        component [Permission Guard] as PermissionGuard
        component [Feature Guard] as FeatureGuard

        component [Auth Service] as FrontendAuthService
        component [API Service] as ApiService
        component [Billing Service] as FrontendBillingService
        component [State Management] as StateManagement
    }

    component [Tailwind CSS] as Tailwind
    component [RxJS] as RxJS
}

note right of Angular
  **Tech Stack:**
  • Angular 17+ (Standalone)
  • TypeScript 5+
  • Tailwind CSS 3+
  • RxJS 7+
  • Signals API

  **Features:**
  • Lazy loading modules
  • SSR ready (Angular Universal)
  • PWA capable
  • Responsive mobile-first
end note

' ===============================================
' CAPA DE API (BACKEND)
' ===============================================

package "API Layer" <<backend>> {
    component "Django REST Framework" as DRF {
        component [Auth Endpoints] as AuthAPI
        component [Users Endpoints] as UsersAPI
        component [Roles Endpoints] as RolesAPI
        component [Permissions Endpoints] as PermissionsAPI
        component [Billing Endpoints] as BillingAPI
        component [Audit Endpoints] as AuditAPI
        component [Webhooks Endpoints] as WebhooksAPI

        component [JWT Middleware] as JWTMiddleware
        component [Tenant Middleware] as TenantMiddleware
        component [Permission Middleware] as PermissionMiddleware
        component [Rate Limit Middleware] as RateLimitMiddleware

        component [Auth Service] as BackendAuthService
        component [Billing Service] as BackendBillingService
        component [RBAC Service] as RBACService
        component [Notification Service] as NotificationService
    }

    component [Django ORM] as ORM
    component [Django Signals] as Signals
    component [Serializers] as Serializers
}

note right of DRF
  **Tech Stack:**
  • Django 5.0+
  • Python 3.11+
  • DRF 3.14+
  • PyJWT
  • bcrypt

  **Patterns:**
  • ViewSets + Routers
  • Serializers con validación
  • Permissions personalizados
  • Signals para eventos
  • Middleware pipeline
end note

' ===============================================
' CAPA DE DATOS (DATABASE)
' ===============================================

package "Data Layer" <<database>> {
    database "PostgreSQL 15+" as PostgreSQL {
        component [Tables] as Tables
        component [Row-Level Security] as RLS
        component [Indexes] as Indexes
        component [Triggers] as Triggers
        component [Partitions] as Partitions
    }

    component [PgBouncer\nConnection Pool] as PgBouncer
    component [pg_stat_statements] as PgStats
}

note bottom of PostgreSQL
  **Features:**
  • Row-Level Security (RLS)
  • JSONB para settings/metadata
  • Full-text search (tsvector)
  • Partitioned tables (audit_log)
  • Composite indexes con tenant_id
  • Foreign keys + constraints

  **Performance:**
  • Connection pooling (10-50)
  • Read replicas (heavy queries)
  • Automatic VACUUM
  • Query optimization monitoring
end note

' ===============================================
' CAPA DE CACHE
' ===============================================

package "Cache Layer" <<cache>> {
    database "Redis 7+" as Redis {
        component [Session Store] as SessionStore
        component [Permissions Cache] as PermissionsCache
        component [Rate Limit Counters] as RateLimitCounters
        component [MFA Pending] as MFAPending
        component [Feature Flags Cache] as FeatureFlagsCache
    }
}

note bottom of Redis
  **Keys Structure:**
  • permissions:{user_id}:{tenant_id}
  • sessions:{session_id}
  • rate_limit:{ip}:{endpoint}
  • mfa_pending:{token}
  • features:{tenant_id}
  • lockout:{email}

  **TTLs:**
  • Permissions: 5 min
  • Sessions: 24 hours
  • Rate limits: 1 min
  • MFA pending: 5 min
  • Features: 5 min
end note

' ===============================================
' CAPA DE TAREAS ASÍNCRONAS
' ===============================================

package "Background Jobs" <<queue>> {
    component "Celery Workers" as Celery {
        component [Email Tasks] as EmailTasks
        component [Billing Tasks] as BillingTasks
        component [Notification Tasks] as NotificationTasks
        component [Cleanup Tasks] as CleanupTasks
        component [Export Tasks] as ExportTasks
    }

    component [Celery Beat\nScheduler] as CeleryBeat
    database "Redis\n(Broker)" as RedisBroker
}

note bottom of Celery
  **Tasks:**
  • send_email(template, data)
  • process_renewals() [daily]
  • retry_payment(tenant_id) [scheduled]
  • generate_invoice_pdf(invoice_id)
  • export_audit_logs(filters)
  • cleanup_expired_tokens() [daily]

  **Scheduling:**
  • Cron-like with Celery Beat
  • Task priority queues
  • Retry with exponential backoff
  • Result backend (Redis)
end note

' ===============================================
' SERVICIOS EXTERNOS
' ===============================================

package "External Services" <<external>> {
    component [Stripe API] as Stripe {
        portin "Charges" as StripeCharges
        portin "Customers" as StripeCustomers
        portin "Subscriptions" as StripeSubs
        portout "Webhooks" as StripeWebhooks
    }

    component [Email Service\n(SendGrid/SES)] as EmailService {
        portin "Send Email" as SendEmail
        portout "Webhooks" as EmailWebhooks
    }

    component [AWS S3] as S3 {
        portin "Upload" as S3Upload
        portin "Download" as S3Download
    }

    component [Monitoring\n(Sentry/DataDog)] as Monitoring {
        portin "Error Tracking" as ErrorTracking
        portin "Performance Metrics" as Metrics
    }
}

note bottom of Stripe
  **Integration:**
  • Stripe Elements (PCI-compliant)
  • Webhook signature verification
  • Idempotency keys
  • Customer portal

  **Events:**
  • invoice.payment_succeeded
  • invoice.payment_failed
  • customer.subscription.deleted
end note

' ===============================================
' INTERFACES Y PROTOCOLOS
' ===============================================

interface "HTTPS\nREST API" as HTTPS
interface "WebSocket\n(future)" as WebSocket
interface "PostgreSQL\nProtocol" as PostgresProtocol
interface "Redis\nProtocol" as RedisProtocol
interface "SMTP/API" as SMTP

' ===============================================
' RELACIONES - FRONTEND → BACKEND
' ===============================================

Angular --> HTTPS : REST calls
HTTPS --> DRF

AuthModule --> FrontendAuthService
DashboardModule --> ApiService
UsersModule --> ApiService
RolesModule --> ApiService
BillingModule --> FrontendBillingService

FrontendAuthService --> HTTPS : POST /auth/login\nPOST /auth/refresh
ApiService --> HTTPS : CRUD operations
FrontendBillingService --> HTTPS : POST /billing/upgrade

AuthInterceptor ..> HTTPS : Inject JWT token
ErrorInterceptor ..> HTTPS : Handle errors
LoadingInterceptor ..> HTTPS : Loading states

AuthGuard ..> FrontendAuthService : Check auth
PermissionGuard ..> FrontendAuthService : Check permissions
FeatureGuard ..> ApiService : Check features

Angular ..> Tailwind : Styles
ApiService ..> RxJS : Observables
StateManagement ..> RxJS : BehaviorSubject

' ===============================================
' RELACIONES - BACKEND → MIDDLEWARE
' ===============================================

HTTPS --> JWTMiddleware : 1. Verify token
JWTMiddleware --> TenantMiddleware : 2. Set tenant context
TenantMiddleware --> PermissionMiddleware : 3. Load permissions
PermissionMiddleware --> RateLimitMiddleware : 4. Check rate limit
RateLimitMiddleware --> AuthAPI : 5. Route to endpoint

AuthAPI --> BackendAuthService
UsersAPI --> RBACService
RolesAPI --> RBACService
PermissionsAPI --> RBACService
BillingAPI --> BackendBillingService
AuditAPI --> RBACService
WebhooksAPI --> BackendBillingService

' ===============================================
' RELACIONES - BACKEND → DATABASE
' ===============================================

DRF --> PostgresProtocol
PostgresProtocol --> PgBouncer : Connection pooling
PgBouncer --> PostgreSQL

ORM --> PostgresProtocol : SQL queries
Signals ..> PostgresProtocol : Trigger actions

PostgreSQL --> Tables
PostgreSQL --> RLS : Tenant isolation
PostgreSQL --> Indexes : Query optimization
PostgreSQL --> Triggers : Auto-actions
PostgreSQL --> Partitions : Large tables

PgStats ..> PostgreSQL : Monitor performance

' ===============================================
' RELACIONES - BACKEND → CACHE
' ===============================================

DRF --> RedisProtocol
RedisProtocol --> Redis

JWTMiddleware ..> PermissionsCache : GET cached perms
TenantMiddleware ..> FeatureFlagsCache : GET features
RateLimitMiddleware ..> RateLimitCounters : INCR counter
BackendAuthService ..> SessionStore : SET/GET sessions
BackendAuthService ..> MFAPending : SET/GET mfa state

' ===============================================
' RELACIONES - BACKEND → CELERY
' ===============================================

BackendAuthService --> EmailTasks : send_verification_email.delay()
BackendBillingService --> BillingTasks : process_renewals.delay()
NotificationService --> NotificationTasks : send_notification.delay()

CeleryBeat --> BillingTasks : Schedule: 0 0 * * *
CeleryBeat --> CleanupTasks : Schedule: 0 2 * * *

Celery --> RedisBroker : Task queue
RedisBroker --> Celery : Task results

' ===============================================
' RELACIONES - CELERY → EXTERNAL
' ===============================================

EmailTasks --> SMTP
SMTP --> EmailService : Send transactional emails

BillingTasks --> StripeCharges : Create charges
BillingTasks --> StripeCustomers : Manage customers
BillingTasks --> StripeSubs : Manage subscriptions

ExportTasks --> S3Upload : Upload PDFs/CSVs

StripeWebhooks --> WebhooksAPI : POST /webhooks/stripe
EmailWebhooks --> WebhooksAPI : POST /webhooks/email

' ===============================================
' RELACIONES - MONITORING
' ===============================================

DRF ..> ErrorTracking : Send errors
DRF ..> Metrics : Send APM data
Angular ..> ErrorTracking : Frontend errors
Angular ..> Metrics : Performance metrics

' ===============================================
' DEPLOYMENT BOUNDARIES
' ===============================================

package "Load Balancer" <<external>> {
    component [Nginx/ALB] as LoadBalancer
}

note top of LoadBalancer
  **Features:**
  • HTTPS termination (TLS 1.3)
  • Request routing
  • Static file serving
  • Rate limiting (IP-based)
  • Health checks
  • SSL certificates (Let's Encrypt)
end note

LoadBalancer --> Angular : Serve SPA
LoadBalancer --> HTTPS : Proxy API requests

' ===============================================
' SECURITY COMPONENTS
' ===============================================

package "Security Layer" {
    component [WAF\n(Web Application Firewall)] as WAF
    component [DDoS Protection\n(Cloudflare)] as DDoS
    component [SSL/TLS\nCertificates] as SSL
}

DDoS --> WAF : Filter malicious traffic
WAF --> LoadBalancer : Clean traffic
SSL ..> LoadBalancer : HTTPS encryption

' ===============================================
' NOTAS ADICIONALES
' ===============================================

note as N1
  **Data Flow Example: Login**
  1. User enters credentials (Angular)
  2. POST /api/v1/auth/login (HTTPS)
  3. JWT Middleware validates (skip, no token yet)
  4. Auth Service validates credentials (bcrypt)
  5. Query user from PostgreSQL (ORM)
  6. Generate JWT tokens (access + refresh)
  7. Store refresh token in PostgreSQL
  8. Cache permissions in Redis (TTL 5min)
  9. Return tokens to frontend
  10. Frontend stores in localStorage
  11. Audit log entry created (async via Signals)
end note

note as N2
  **Data Flow Example: Billing Renewal**
  1. Celery Beat triggers daily cron (00:00 UTC)
  2. process_renewals() task executes
  3. Query tenants to renew (PostgreSQL)
  4. For each tenant:
     a. Create charge (Stripe API)
     b. Update subscription dates (PostgreSQL)
     c. Create invoice (PostgreSQL)
     d. Generate PDF (export task → S3)
     e. Send email (email task → SendGrid)
  5. Stripe webhook confirms payment
  6. Webhook handler updates status
  7. Cache invalidation (Redis)
end note

' ===============================================
' LEYENDA
' ===============================================

legend right
  |= Color |= Layer |
  | <back:#E3F2FD>   </back> | Frontend (Angular) |
  | <back:#F3E5F5>   </back> | Backend (Django) |
  | <back:#FFF3E0>   </back> | Database (PostgreSQL) |
  | <back:#E8F5E9>   </back> | Cache (Redis) |
  | <back:#FFF9C4>   </back> | Queue (Celery) |
  | <back:#FCE4EC>   </back> | External Services |

  |= Symbol |= Meaning |
  | → | Synchronous call |
  | ..> | Asynchronous call |
  | —— | Component boundary |

  **Protocols:**
  • HTTPS: REST API (JSON)
  • WebSocket: Real-time (future)
  • PostgreSQL: SQL queries
  • Redis: Key-value commands
  • SMTP: Email delivery
endlegend

@enduml
